name: SHA-3
description: !!python/str " SHA-3, a subset of the cryptographic primitive family\
  \ Keccak. SHA-3 uses the sponge construction, in which message blocks are XORed\
  \ into a subset of the state, which is then transformed as a whole. In the version\
  \ used in SHA-3, the state consists of a 5\xD75 array of 64-bit words, 1600 bits\
  \ total."
